                                                                 Rev. 6

                                 |CKBUNIQUES
                                 |BKB=======

|CKBIntroduction:
|BKB-------------
|WKOThe purpose of this document is to define exceptional and unique objects
as well as to state regulations governing their implementations into DW.
This document is considered law and no exceptions are to be made.


|CKBDefinitions:
|BKB------------

|YKBUnique      |BKB- |WKOAny weapon, armour, or object that performs some function
              that cannot logically be explained by normal laws of 
              physics, given the medieval technological level of 
              Darkwind.  An item is considered unique if it exceeds the 
              limits contained in ANY document pertaining to that 
              particular item AND exceeds the rules governing 
              exceptional items (see definition below). This can include 
              but is not limited to the object's inherent qualities.
              All new uniquesmust first be approved for balance before 
              implementation.  An item can be made unique without it being 
              required to be unique.

|YKBExceptional |BKB- |WKOAny weapon, armour, or object that performs some function
              more efficiently or with more positive benefits to the 
              player (or objects that use it) or more severe
              consequences to whatever is targeted by the item as 
              regulated in documents containing guidelines for standard
              related objects.  The nature of an exceptional can be but 
              is not limited to the craftsmanship or philosphy regarding 
              the object or its use or lack of (if beneficial). 


|CKBRegulations:
|BKB-----------

|YKBUnique      |BKB- |WKOIt is the policy of Darkwind that wizards are allowed at
              most one unique class object per 100 rooms.  Such items
              must be created using |YKOmake_unique_object()|WKO.

|WKBExceptional |BKB- |WKOIt is the policy of Darkwind that wizards are allowed at
              most 15% of their items to be of exceptional quality.     
              This 15% is 15% of all weapons, and armour.  If an object 
              is not a weapon or armour but is still considered         
              exceptional, then that item counts as part of the 15% of  
              all weapons and armours.  This 15% is also a percentage   
              of the total number in your area at any one time.         
              Weapons, armour, and exceptional objects all contribute   
              to the same 15%. For a 100 room area, this would be a total
              of 15 items, including a unique.


|CKBFurther Regulations:
|BKB--------------------

|YKBWeapons:
          |WKOThe following qualities will make a weapon exceptional:
          
          |MKBQuality greater than 30.
          Material composition containing MAT_ADAMANTITE.
          A dodge bonus of 1.
          A hit bonus of 1.
          Gives one level of light/darkness.
          |WKB^|MKBAny stat changes that are not net increases.
          Allowing use by a normally restricted guilds.
          |WKB^|MKBAn extra damage type on hit, ie DAM_GOOD.
          |WKB^|MKBWeapon hits (see below)

          
          |WKOThe following qualities will make a weapon unique:
          
          |WKB^|MKBQuality greater than 50.
          |WKB^|MKBAny 2 exceptional qualities.
          |WKB^|MKBAny kind of healing.
          |WKB^|MKBAny kind of increase in damage resistance, ie DAM_GOOD
                or DAM_PIERCE.
          |WKB^|MKBA dodge bonus greater than 1.
          |WKB^|MKBA hit bonus greater than 1.
          |WKB^|MKBGives more than 1 level of light/darkness.
          |WKB^|MKBAny extra attacks/damage.
          |WKB^|MKBAny net stat increases.
          |WKB^|MKBArmor piercing damage, or 2 or more extra damage types.
          |WKB^|MKBWeapon hits (see below)


          |WKOThe following are just not allowed, period:
          
          |RKBWeapons may not sober a player.
          Weapons may not make a player unsatiated.
          Weapons may not lower a player's Soft level.
          Weapons may not have a quality over 100.
          **Weapons may not modify combat via the use of tmp_to.
          Any weapon modification. ie: set_flaming
          Weapons may not have a hit bonus of greater than 5.
          Weapons may not have a dodge bonus of greater than 5.


        |WKB* |YKOA weapon can contain a weapon_hit function without being
          considered unique. If the hit_function does no additional damage,
          then that item is not considered exceptional. It should be noted
          that the coding wizard should not have an excess amount of
          weapons yielding hit messages as it defeats the purpose of the 
          message. If the weapon_hit function returns any value other than
          0 (thus a bonus on damage), the weapon is considered exceptional.
          If the weapon_hit is greater than 1, the weapon is considered
          unique. This applies for the greatest possible bonus, not the
          average.

       |WKB** |YKOSome items will be able to use the tmp_to modifiers. This is
          done on a case-by-case basis through a review of the wizards
          IMP+ and must have valid reason. ie unique rewards on boss mobs.
          
        |WKB^ |YKOCharacterstics denoted with this symbol must be
              set_no_save(1) in the reset function. As you can see
              all uniques qualify for this. While the make_unique_object
              code will handle this, it's just good form to put it into
              the code to be safe.

|CKBArmour:
          |WKOThe following qualities will make an armor exceptional:
          
          |MKBQuality greater than 30.
          A dodge bonus of 1.
          |MKBAny stat bonuses:
          |WKB    1 stat from level 1 to 44.
          |WKB    3 stats from 46 to 64.
          |WKB    5 stats from 65+.
          |MKBAny single damage resistance:
          |WKB    1 resist from level 1 to 44.
          |WKB    3 resist from 46 to 64.
          |WKB    5 resist from 65+.
          |MKBGives one level of light/darkness.
          |MKBA ring/amulet of AC 1 or 2.
          |MKBAllowing use by normally restricted guilds.
          
          
          |WKOThe following qualities will make an armor unique:
          
          |WKB^|MKBQuality greater than 50.
          |WKB^|MKBAny 2 exceptional qualities.
          |WKB^|MKBAny dodge bonus of more than 1.
          |WKB^|MKBAny stat bonus of more than 5.
          |WKB^|MKBAny resistance of more than 5.
          |WKB^|MKBMultiple damage resistances.
          |WKB^|MKBAny resistance to a physical damage type (DAM_SLASH etc.)
          |WKB^|MKBA ring/amulet AC of 3 or more.
          |WKB^|MKBGives more than 1 level of light/darkness.
          
  
          |WKOThe following are just not allowed, period:

          |RKBArmour may not sober a player.
          Armour may not make a player unsatiated.
          Armour may not lower a player's Soft level.
          Armour may not have a quality over 100.
          **Armour may not modify combat via the use of tmp_to.
          Any permanant armour modification. ie set_thorned(1)
          
       |WKB** |YKOSome items will be able to use the tmp_to modifiers. This is
          done on a case-by-case basis through a review of the wizards
          IMP+ and must have valid reason. ie unique rewards on boss mobs.
          
       |WKB^ |YKOCharacterstics denoted with this symbol must be
              set_no_save(1) in the reset function. As you can see
              all uniques qualify for this. While the make_unique_object
              code will handle this, it's just good form to put it into
              the code to be safe.
          
|CKBObjects:
          |WKOThe following qualities will make an object exceptional:
          
          |MKBGiving two (or more) levels of light/darkness.
          |WKB^|MKBAny stat increases.
          |WKB^|MKBAny kind of added resistance/weakness.
          Quality greater than 30.
          |WKB^|MKBAny extra damage/attacks.
          
          |WKO following are just not allowed, period:
          
          |RKBObjects may not have a quality over 100.
          Objects may not modify combat via the use of tmp_to.
          Objects may not have more than 1 qualifying characteristic.

       |WKB^ |YKOCharacterstics denoted with this symbol must be
              set_no_save(1) in the reset function. As you can see
              all uniques qualify for this. While the make_unique_object
              code will handle this, it's just good form to put it into
              the code to be safe.

|CKBConclusions:
|BKB============

|WKOThe purpose of this doc is not to target any one person in particular.
It is to provide guildelines and regulations regarding objects. This
doc can be revised at any time. Such revision will follow with posts to
the wizboards. If you are unsure about the classification of an object,
please talk to an IMP+. In addition, please provide a variety of strengths
in the objects you place in your areas. Not everyone in every situation
could possiblyhave the upper limits of all standard weapons and armour.
A lot of times, kewl hit messages or even just a kewl looking weapon
is enough to make it popular.

Also note that there are very few rules concerning how good a unique item
can be. This should not be taken to mean that uniques can be infinitely
powerful, but rather that the power of uniques is often hard to quantify.
Overly powerful uniques may be downgraded/removed at any time. This will
be decided by the wizards at IMP+.
          
          
|CKBRevision History:
BKB----------------
|WKORev. 6 - Changed to reflect even newer standards and include
         objects. Color also added.

Rev. 5 - Changed to reflect new weapon/armor standards.

Rev. 4 - Added requirements for submitting uniques for review.
         All changes are marked with a | at the far right side
         of the doc.

Rev. 3 - Fixed some typos, edited a few of the classifications to
         reflect the way they've been used on the mud; namely, the
         add_resistance for armour, the set_guild_allow for weapons
         and armour, and the AC of amulets.

Rev. 2 - Added clarifications to the 15% exceptional rule.  Also
         made clarification to the hit_func damage occurance
         limits for exceptionals.

Rev. 1 - Added clarification as to making uniques.

Rev. 0 - Initial release
